        <descriptionSet>
            <description source="Millon, Henry A. and Craig Hugh Smyth. Michelangelo Architect: The Facade of San Lorenzo and the Drum and Dome of Saint Peter’s. Milan: Olivetti, 1988. Page: 89." dataDate="2016-05-19-12-42-14">
                <text>This is probably one of the two models described by Michelangelo in a letter to his brother, Lionardo, in September 1555. His designs for the façade had begun in 1515.</text>
                <author>
                    <name refid="131347215" type="corporate" vocab="viaf">Visual Resources Association</name>
                    <role type="code" vocab="marcrelator">edt</role>
                </author>
            </description>
            <description source="Casa Buonarroti [website], http://www.casabuonarroti.it/ (accessed 3/2/2009)" href="http://core.vraweb.org/examples/html/example004_full_xml.html">Michelangelo's design of the facade went through three main phases, which can be identified in three drawings in the collection of Casa Buonarroti, nos. 45A, 47A and 43A. In all likelihood it was the clearly defined image in the last of these drawings that was translated into the large wooden model in Casa Buonarroti, which itself reflects the passage from the design stage to that of execution, as specified in the contract drawn up between Leo X and the artist on January 19, 1518. The model is 1:12 scale. The facade was never built.</description>
            	<author>
                    <name refid="131347215" type="corporate" vocab="viaf">Visual Resources Association</name>
